Sean R. Meyer

Scientist | Developer | Designer

I am a Lead Data Scientist at Precision Health, University of Michigan, and Health Information Technology & Services (HITS), Michigan Medicine. I work with stakeholders to develop, implement, evaluate, and monitor prediction models in clinical and administrative workflows to improve patient outcomes. As a Clinical Intelligence Committee member, he designs prediction modeling implementation processes, drafts policies concerning model governance, and provides ad-hoc analytics for institutional initiatives.

While pursuing my doctorate, I studied clinical early warning systems. I developed a design process for preparing time-series EHR data intended for machine learning algorithms, with a dissertation titled Developing and Applying a Design Framework to Prepare Electronic Health Record Data for Time-Series Modeling. I worked with clinical partners to create a predictive model to predict postpartum hemorrhage that outperformed existing systems used in maternal care at Michigan Medicine. I co-authored and applied an open-source framework for building a data pipeline that engineers features based on pre-defined design elements. My passion for this work stems from my interest in transforming research discoveries into bedside care through health IT and data science.

Experience

Lead Data Scientist | Precision Health, University of Michigan and Health Information Technology & Services, Michigan Medicine | September 2022 - present

Senior Scientist | Michigan Institute for Data Science, University of Michigan | November 2021 - September 2022

Doctoral Student | College of Engineering, University of Michigan | Sept 2017 - August 2021

Battle Captain | U.S. Army | July 2016 – June 2017

Business Intelligence Analyst | School of Dentistry, University of Michigan | March 2012 – July 2016

Education

PhD | Design Science | University of Michigan

MS | Design Science | University of Michigan

MBA | Business Administration, Enterprise Business Intelligence | Eastern Michigan University

BS | Computer Science | Eastern Michigan University

AAS | Interactive Web Design | Washtenaw Community College
